<subSubSection id="C3306539FFA7776CFF1FF998FD329021" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9536B2FFA7776CFF1FF998FD329021" blockId="27.[151,1437,1485,1908]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFF1FF998FEE09079" bold="true" box="[199,322,1557,1583]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The calling song of the species does not consist of a homogenous sequence of echemes as in all other known species of the group, but the very short echemes are grouped in small series of three echemes separated from the next series by a larger interval (
<figureCitation id="13112A37FFA7776CFDF9F9D0FDC79021" box="[545,613,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1988,2012]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,672,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-293@16.[151,1436,669,1965]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Oscillograms of the calling songs of species of the Mecopoda confracta subgroup. Overview (12 s sections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141299/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13112A37FFA7776CFDAAF9D0FD209021" box="[626,642,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1241,1265]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,188,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[180,1407,181,1216]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 9. Oscillograms of the calling songs of species of the Mecopoda confracta subgroup. Details (1 s sections). In M. sismondoi sp. nov. synchronous registration of movement of left tegmen and sound (upper line: upward deflection indicating opening, downward closing; lower line: sound)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141303/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3306539FFA7776CFF1FF90CFE28915E" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9536B2FFA7776CFF1FF90CFA2290CD" blockId="27.[151,1437,1485,1908]" box="[199,1408,1665,1692]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFF1FF90CFEFB90CD" bold="true" box="[199,345,1665,1691]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Description.</emphasis>
Morphologically no difference to other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D31FFA7776CFC62F90FFBE990CD" box="[954,1099,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confracta">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFC62F90FFBE990CD" box="[954,1099,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">M. confracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B43FFA7776CFB11F90CFAD790CD" author="Liu, C. - X. &amp; Heller, K. - G. &amp; Wang, X. - S. &amp; Yang, Z. &amp; Wu, C. &amp; Liu, F. &amp; Zhang, T." box="[1225,1397,1665,1691]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" pagination="296 - 310" refId="ref25603" refString="Liu, C. - X., Heller, K. - G., Wang, X. - S., Yang, Z., Wu, C., Liu, F. &amp; Zhang, T. (2020) Taxonomy of a katydid genus Mecopoda Serville (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Mecopodinae) from East Asia. Zootaxa, 4758 (2), 296 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4758.2.5" type="journal article" year="2020">
Liu 
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFB21F90FFA9390CD" box="[1273,1329,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536B2FFA7776CFF1FF928FAD790E9" blockId="27.[151,1437,1485,1908]" box="[199,1397,1701,1728]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFF1FF928FED490E9" bold="true" box="[199,374,1701,1727]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Measurements</emphasis>
(in mm): pronotum length 8; tegmen length 56; tegmen width 13.5; hind femora length 43.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536B2FFA7776CFF1FF944FE28915E" blockId="27.[151,1437,1485,1908]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFF1FF944FED990B5" bold="true" box="[199,379,1737,1763]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
2n = 29, FN = 52; pairs 1, 4 and 6–14 metacentric, 2, 3 and 5 acrocentric, X chromosome metacentric (
<figureCitation id="13112A37FFA7776CFEF1F960FEDE915E" box="[297,380,1773,1800]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[261,1329,186,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-19@27.[249,1338,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15. C-banded karyotypes (left side) and mitotic metaphase (right side) of five Mecopoda species with different chromosome number (2n). Karyotypes are reconstructed by arranging homologous chromosomes in order of decreasing size. X, sex chromosome." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141316/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3306539FFA7776CFF1FF89CFC4B9125" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9536B2FFA7776CFF1FF89CFC4B9125" blockId="27.[151,1437,1485,1908]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA0FFA7776CFF1FF89CFE06917D" bold="true" box="[199,420,1809,1835]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Derivatio nominis.</emphasis>
Name remembering to the Indian monk Mahinda who arrived in Mihintale, the 
<typeStatus id="54918810FFA7776CFAFDF89FFAF7917A" box="[1317,1365,1810,1836]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">type</typeStatus>
locality, according to religious myths traveling through the air, founding Buddhism in 
<collectingCountry id="F33D7622FFA7776CFBF7F8B8FB039119" box="[1071,1185,1845,1871]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. The insect was found on the stupa which was built to celebrate this event. Substantive in genitive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
